title: [Caligos Isle, Lighthouse Path]
description: A twisted, winding path is just discernible between the jagged rocks stabbing at the sky.  Silvery-hued mists settle between the rocks battling the constant crash of waves to claim domain here, leaving you coated in a salty mist.   A long-abandoned lighthouse stands at the point where shore meets sea, silhouetted in the darkness against the silvery white, moonlit horizon.

A twisted, winding path is just discernible between the jagged rocks stabbing at the sky.  The click-clack of crabs and the scuttle of small, jointed feet are barely heard over the constant crash of the waves against the spires.  A long-abandoned lighthouse stands at the point where shore meets sea, silhouetted against waves on the horizon.
